 BY TIMOTHY AGBOR, OSOGBO The governor of Osun State, Adegboyega Oyetola has offered his condolences to the lawmaker representing Oyo Central Senatorial District, Teslim Folarin over the demise of his wife, Angela Nwaka, who died on Friday. Oyetola, in a statement released by his Chief Press Secretary, Ismail Omipidan, on Saturday in Osogbo, expressed sadness over her death. He described the incident as shocking and sad, and urged the family, especially the bereaved husband to accept the incident as the will of Allah. The governor equally extended his heartfelt condolences to the government and people of Oyo State, particularly the people of Oyo Central Senatorial District and all other persons affected by the death of Barrister Angela. He said, “I, on behalf of my family, government and people of Osun, offer my heartfelt condolences to the Teslim Folarin family and share their grief at such a time as this. “May Almighty Allah comfort the entire family, give them the fortitude to bear the loss and accept the soul of the departed.” 